      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(providers): add experimental apple-vz provider for local Linux VMs",
        "body": "Fixes https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/262.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds the built-in `apple-vz` provider for full ARM64 Ubuntu VMs on Apple Silicon Macs running macOS 13 or newer.\n\nApple VZ is direct and local-only. It uses Apple `Virtualization.framework`, exposes guest SSH through a loopback VSOCK proxy, and plugs into the normal Crabbox SSH-lease workflow:\n\n- `warmup`\n- `run`\n- `ssh`\n- `status`\n- `list`\n- `stop`\n- `cleanup`\n\n## What ships\n\n- Provider registration, config, flags, defaults, and Ubuntu ARM64 image mapping.\n- Native `crabbox-apple-vz-helper` packaged beside the CLI in GoReleaser archives and Homebrew installs.\n- Verified image download and cache, bounded QCOW2 conversion, sparse per-lease disks, NoCloud seed generation, EFI boot, NAT, VSOCK SSH, and retained leases.\n- Content-addressed managed helper installation with ad-hoc signing, required entitlements, integrity digests, use locks, and safe old-version cleanup.\n- Full provider docs, configuration reference, troubleshooting, security model, limits, and live-smoke support.\n\n## Hardening\n\nPre-merge review expanded this substantially beyond the original implementation:\n\n- Atomic, checksum-keyed image caches with cancellation, size limits, redirect policy, local-file identity, backing-file rejection, and interrupted-preparation recovery.\n- Rollback and diagnostics for every startup phase; metadata-less cleanup; stale-start recovery; bounded helper termination.\n- Collision-resistant Darwin kernel process identity before signaling, plus verified migration of older `ps` identities.\n- Active image preparation is visible as `starting`; SSH fields remain empty until a real endpoint exists.\n- Secret-safe signed image URL handling through stdin; remote images require HTTPS and SHA-256.\n- Strict CPU, memory, disk, user, path, helper, host architecture, and macOS-version validation.\n- Retained leases remain controllable when the configured source helper moves or disappears.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal CI-equivalent gate:\n\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- module tests\n- core coverage: `90.1%`\n- Apple VZ provider coverage: `73.5%`\n- 25 consecutive race-test runs for helper and provider packages\n- Windows amd64 and Linux arm64 cross-builds\n- 113 script tests\n- docs command-surface, link, and site-build checks\n- GoReleaser snapshot build\n- autoreview clean after all accepted findings\n\nExact packaged artifact:\n\n- Commit: `491174de5c86d6009d0834ad775c6a32f1db6734`\n- Version: `0.28.0-SNAPSHOT-491174de`\n- Darwin ARM64 archive SHA-256: `e808a57cedb9529070e4964977bc2f1d3792fd4c9f131b332fbe8ca2c9a6f315`\n\nPhysical Apple Silicon live E2E:\n\n- macOS 26.5 arm64, `kern.hv_support=1`\n- lease `cbx_f7f9e6d97a18`\n- created Ubuntu ARM64 VM, reached SSH readiness, synced 737 repository files, verified systemd and source visibility, ran the command, auto-deleted, and returned an empty provider list\n- verified private state/cache permissions and managed-helper codesign entitlements\n\nClean Parallels macOS guest:\n\n- downloaded and checksum-verified the same archive\n- verified native arm64 binaries, embedded version, managed-helper digest, signing, entitlements, and permissions\n- doctor reached the expected nested-virtualization boundary only: Parallels reported `kern.hv_support=0`\n\n## Scope\n\n- Apple Silicon macOS 13+\n- Linux ARM64 guests\n- local direct provider; no broker or cloud account\n- no desktop, browser, VNC, Tailscale, checkpoint, fork, or restore surface\n",
        "branch": "codex/applevz-startup-runtime-fixes",
